Q: How to change icon (SF Symbol) color in SwiftUI TabView item A: <p>In SwiftUI <code>TabView</code>, the unselected SF Symbol color comes from <code>UITabBarAppearance</code> <strong>and you must set it for all layouts + apply it to <code>scrollEdgeAppearance</code> too</strong> (otherwise you’ll often still get the default black icon).</p>
<p>Here is the code:</p>
<pre><code>import SwiftUI

@main
struct TestApp: App {
    init() {
        let appearance = UITabBarAppearance()
        appearance.configureWithDefaultBackground()

        // Unselected (normal)
        let normal = appearance.stackedLayoutAppearance.normal
        normal.iconColor = .systemBlue
        normal.titleTextAttributes = [.foregroundColor: UIColor.systemBlue]

        // (Optional) selected
        let selected = appearance.stackedLayoutAppearance.selected
        selected.iconColor = .systemRed
        selected.titleTextAttributes = [.foregroundColor: UIColor.systemRed]

        // If you use iPad / different size classes, set these too:
        appearance.inlineLayoutAppearance.normal.iconColor = .systemBlue
        appearance.inlineLayoutAppearance.normal.titleTextAttributes = [.foregroundColor: UIColor.systemBlue]
